Ten people were reportedly killed after a bus lost control, overturning in a stream before hitting a bridge on the N3 toll road between Heidelberg and Villiers in Mpumalanga. The incident happened on Sunday, 29 May at about 5am. Mpumalanga Community Safety Security and Liaison spokesman Moeti Mmusi confirmed that three people sustained critical injuries. “The nine other people died at the scene. The cause of the crash remains unclear at this stage. However, the crash investigation teams have already been sent to the scene to commence with the probe,” he said. “Mpumalanga Community Safety, Security and Liaison MEC Vusi Shongwe noted with a deep sense of regret unabated loss of life on our roads as a result of crashes. “More details will be made available later. The paramedics are still at the scene.” He said the MEC is therefore appealing to motorists to use the road with greater caution. “This needless loss of lives must come to an end. We must all actively participate in preventing these deadly crashes.” He has sent heartfelt condolences to the bereaved families as well as wishing those who were injured a speedy recovery. The number of those who were killed in the bus crash has increased to ten. The bus driver and his assistant have succumed to thier injuries.